Text.Value: Of course you will. Ta-ta.
Ponder the ins and outs of your contract. Could there be a loophole?
Interesting. Now why should I go letting my favourite pet off his leash?
How about I let the cult infect this devil instead? I bet they'd make a loyal thrall.
Drop the attitude and perk up your ears - you've got a new mission.
What do you want, Mizora?
If this devil is so powerful, how did they manage to get captured?
*Mizora's words may be flippant, but they are tinged with desperation. She cannot afford for you to fail this mission.*
I've never seen such a fearless display of sheer idiocy. Bravo!
Now to Moonrise, pet. And do mind the shadows - they've been especially hungry.
Ha. Haha. Hahahahahaha!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Laughing hysterically that a player tried a children's incantation to release themselves from a devil's contract.
EditorData.NodeContext: Mizora is still in her pod, laughing hysterically at the player

Text.Value: I'll do it on one condition: you free me from this infernal pact.
Fine, I'll play your game. But I amend the pact once the mission's done - not before.
Never mind. I'll free Zariel's asset.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The party stops as they walk through shadow-cursed town

Text.Value: Such a good boy you are - I've trained you well. But a quick review of the rules wouldn't hurt.
Compliance. Just as it should be.
Playtime's over, pet.
Clause Z, Section Thirteen - the 'Lemure' clause. Could've sworn we covered this.
*This may be your best chance to negotiate your way out of your pact.*
Incredible - you actually think you hold the winning hand.
*Your own contract is airtight. But you recall an old incantation from a children's story, said to void a devil's pact: 'Abi, diabole, et nunquam redi.'*
Is that so? Give me one reason why I shouldn't let them rot.
Now be a good boy and play fetch, pup - or you'll spend an eternity sizzling in the Hells.
Questions, questions - you're wasting my time. Let's see about getting your priorities fixed.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mizora's holographic image sinks into the devilish circle and it closes behind.

Text.Value: I will make sure it's done.
Ugh - heartbreaking. I bet you thought I'd be impressed.
'Abi, diabole, et nunquam redi.'

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: A diabolical circle starts to draw itself on the ground. Our of it rises a hologram of Mizora, though not Mizora herself.

Text.Value: They're locked up in the cult's fortress, Moonrise Towers. And you're getting 'em out.
Ahem. Clause Z, Section Thirteen: 'Should promised soul refuse obeyance or neglect duty, the pact-holder shall cast the promised into Avernus as a lemure.'
Hells - I'm on my way.
Say you know a pact-breaking charm and chant a series of pseudo-Infernal phrases.
Absolute's cult has gone and grabbed one of Zariel's assets. A devil - and a powerful one at that.
*You can think of no way to void a devil's pact.*
Ahh, I love this time of year. The dickheads start popping up wherever you look.

EditorData.NodeContext: Like she's talking about flowers, but she's talking about Mizora, who she hates, and who's just popped into their camp uninvited

Text.Value: I'll make it simple: you fail or refuse, and you turn to a thick blob of stink-flesh and sink to Avernus.
And this is my problem how, exactly?
Forget it. This 'asset' can rot in there for all I care.
Clause F, Section Nine: 'Soul-binder shall bestow reward or favour only upon soul-bearer's fulfilment of related obligation.'
I'd start caring - and quick, sunshine.

Synopsis: Mizora contacts Wyll after she's been captured by the cultists. Not a lot of choices here, but you can try and find out how she got caught and express opinion on getting her out.
